      <span class="eyebrow">Why now</span>
      <h2>Leicester already has the ingredients — this week puts them on one stage.</h2>
      <p>Research excellence, business infrastructure, and public reach already exist across the city. The Week is an amplifier, not a new start: it turns three established strengths into one unmissable programme.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars">
      <div class="pillar">
        <span class="num">01 — Heritage</span>
        <h3>65 years in orbit</h3>
        <p>The University of Leicester's first instrument flew in 1961, and a Leicester-built presence in space has continued since 1967.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <span class="num">02 — Infrastructure</span>
        <h3>A working Space City</h3>
        <p>Space Park Leicester is a live hub for research, industry, and enterprise — built with the University, industry, and government.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <span class="num">03 — Momentum</span>
        <h3>A growth-strategy priority</h3>
        <p>Space and Earth observation are named beacon sectors in the region's economic growth strategy, alongside a national space strategy pushing the same ambitions.</p>
      </div>
